{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_87","type":"agent_message","text":"Fixed two things.\n\n`generateMetadata` now runs `splitTestOnlyMetadata` automatically after `metadataCopy`, so the exact reproduction flow no longer leaves test-only entries in library metadata. That change is in [MetadataGenerationUtils.java](/home/jovan/Work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/4555-52dcfb52/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java) with the matching assertion in [GenerateMetadataTaskTests.java](/home/jovan/Work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/4555-52dcfb52/tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/GenerateMetadataTaskTests.java). For `software.amazon.awssdk:third-party-jackson-core:2.34.0`, the generated library metadata is now the clean reflection entry in [reachability-metadata.json](/home/jovan/Work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/4555-52dcfb52/metadata/software.amazon.awssdk/third-party-jackson-core/2.34.0/reachability-metadata.json), while the test-only resources were moved into [the test native-image metadata file](/home/jovan/Work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/4555-52dcfb52/tests/src/software.amazon.awssdk/third-party-jackson-core/2.34.0/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json). The regenerated [user-code-filter.json](/home/jovan/Work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/4555-52dcfb52/tests/src/software.amazon.awssdk/third-party-jackson-core/2.34.0/user-code-filter.json) now includes the test package, which is fine because the split step handles those entries.\n\nVerified with:\n- `./gradlew :tck-build-logic:test --tests org.graalvm.internal.tck.GenerateMetadataTaskTests`\n- `./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=software.amazon.awssdk:third-party-jackson-core:2.34.0 --agentAllowedPackages=fromJar`\n- `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles test -Pcoordinates=software.amazon.awssdk:third-party-jackson-core:2.34.0`\n\nOn this machine I had to run Gradle with a working GraalVM combo in the environment; the default local `GRAALVM_HOME` does not have a usable `native-image-agent`."}}
